    ('Dal Tadka', 'Rinse 1 cup toor dal and pressure cook with 3 cups water, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 3/4 tsp salt for 3-4 whistles until soft; Whisk the dal smooth and add hot water to reach a pourable consistency; keep on a low simmer; For the tempering, heat 2 tbsp ghee and add 1 tsp cumin, 4 sliced garlic cloves, 2 dry red chillies and a pinch of asafoetida; fry until golden; Pour the sizzling tempering over the dal; Simmer 5 minutes, finish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve hot with rice or roti', 'toor dal, ghee, cumin, garlic, dry red chilli, asafoetida, turmeric, salt, coriander leaves'),
