    ('Aloo Paratha', 'Knead a soft dough with 2 cups flour, 1/2 tsp salt, 1 tsp oil and about 3/4 cup water; cover and rest 20 minutes; Divide into 6 balls; roll out, stuffing with spiced mashed potato if required, and dust with dry flour; Cook on a hot tawa 1-2 minutes per side, brushing with ghee, until golden brown spots appear and it puffs; Serve warm with curd, pickle or curry', 'spiced mashed potato, whole wheat flour, salt, oil, ghee, water'),
