    ('Upma', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the semolina with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'semolina, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Rava Kesari', 'Cook the semolina with 2 cups full-fat milk and 1 tbsp ghee on low heat, stirring often so it doesn''t catch; When it thickens, add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 tsp cardamom powder; keep stirring 8-10 minutes; Cook until it leaves the sides of the pan and turns glossy; Garnish with 2 tbsp chopped nuts; serve warm or chilled', 'semolina, sugar, milk, ghee, cardamom, chopped nuts'),
    ('Pesarattu', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the green gram with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'green gram, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
