    ('Idiyappam', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the rice flour with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'rice flour, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Sambar', 'Rinse 1 cup lentils and vegetables and pressure cook with 3 cups water, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 3/4 tsp salt for 3-4 whistles until soft; Whisk the dal smooth and add hot water to reach a pourable consistency; keep on a low simmer; For the tempering, heat 2 tbsp ghee and add 1 tsp cumin, 4 sliced garlic cloves, 2 dry red chillies and a pinch of asafoetida; fry until golden; Pour the sizzling tempering over the dal; Simmer 5 minutes, finish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve hot with rice or roti', 'lentils and vegetables, ghee, cumin, garlic, dry red chilli, asafoetida, turmeric, salt, coriander leaves'),
    ('Rasam', 'Rinse 1 cup tamarind and tomato and pressure cook with 3 cups water, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 3/4 tsp salt for 3-4 whistles until soft; Whisk the dal smooth and add hot water to reach a pourable consistency; keep on a low simmer; For the tempering, heat 2 tbsp ghee and add 1 tsp cumin, 4 sliced garlic cloves, 2 dry red chillies and a pinch of asafoetida; fry until golden; Pour the sizzling tempering over the dal; Simmer 5 minutes, finish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve hot with rice or roti', 'tamarind and tomato, ghee, cumin, garlic, dry red chilli, asafoetida, turmeric, salt, coriander leaves'),
    ('Tomato Rasam', 'Rinse 1 cup tomato and pressure cook with 3 cups water, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 3/4 tsp salt for 3-4 whistles until soft; Whisk the dal smooth and add hot water to reach a pourable consistency; keep on a low simmer; For the tempering, heat 2 tbsp ghee and add 1 tsp cumin, 4 sliced garlic cloves, 2 dry red chillies and a pinch of asafoetida; fry until golden; Pour the sizzling tempering over the dal; Simmer 5 minutes, finish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve hot with rice or roti', 'tomato, ghee, cumin, garlic, dry red chilli, asafoetida, turmeric, salt, coriander leaves'),
    ('Pepper Rasam', 'Rinse 1 cup black pepper and pressure cook with 3 cups water, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 3/4 tsp salt for 3-4 whistles until soft; Whisk the dal smooth and add hot water to reach a pourable consistency; keep on a low simmer; For the tempering, heat 2 tbsp ghee and add 1 tsp cumin, 4 sliced garlic cloves, 2 dry red chillies and a pinch of asafoetida; fry until golden; Pour the sizzling tempering over the dal; Simmer 5 minutes, finish with chopped coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve hot with rice or roti', 'black pepper, ghee, cumin, garlic, dry red chilli, asafoetida, turmeric, salt, coriander leaves'),
    ('Avial', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a heavy pan; add 1 large finely chopped onion and saute 5-6 minutes until golden brown; Add 1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste and cook 1 minute until the raw smell disappears; Add 2 pureed tomatoes (or 3 tbsp tomato paste) and cook 4-5 minutes until the oil separates at the edges; Stir in 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; cook 1 minute; Add the mixed vegetables and coconut with about 3/4 cup water, cover and simmer 10-12 minutes until cooked through and the gravy thickens; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp garam masala, swirl in 2 tbsp cream or whisked yogurt, and finish with chopped coriander; serve hot', 'mixed vegetables and coconut, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
