    ('Veg Spring Roll', 'Mix the shredded vegetables with 1 finely chopped onion, 1 green chilli, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1/2 tsp chilli powder and salt; bind well; Shape into even portions, or dip in a thick gram-flour batter; Heat oil to 170-180C and fry in small batches 3-4 minutes until golden and crisp; Drain on paper towels; serve hot with green chutney', 'shredded vegetables, gram flour, rice flour, green chilli, ginger, turmeric, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Veg Momos', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the cabbage and carrot with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'cabbage and carrot, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Paneer Momos', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the paneer with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'paneer, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Dhokla', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the gram flour with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'gram flour, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Khaman', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the gram flour with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'gram flour, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Khandvi', 'Soak 2 cups rice with 1/2 cup urad dal for 4-6 hours; grind to a smooth batter and ferment overnight; Mix in the gram flour and yogurt with 3/4 tsp salt and a little water to a pourable (or idli) consistency; Heat a greased griddle (or idli steamer); pour and spread thin, or steam 10-12 minutes; Cook until golden and crisp, or fluffy and set; Serve hot with coconut chutney and sambar', 'gram flour and yogurt, rice, urad dal, salt, oil, mustard seeds, curry leaves'),
    ('Handvo', 'Make the batter for the lentils and bottle gourd: whisk 1.5 cups flour with 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 cup sugar and the wet ingredients until smooth; Pour or press into a greased tin lined with parchment; Bake in a preheated 180C oven for 25-30 minutes until risen and a skewer comes out clean; Cool 10 minutes before slicing and serving', 'lentils and bottle gourd, refined flour, sugar, butter, baking powder, vanilla, salt'),
    ('Kachori', 'Mix the spiced lentils with 1 finely chopped onion, 1 green chilli, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1/2 tsp chilli powder and salt; bind well; Shape into even portions, or dip in a thick gram-flour batter; Heat oil to 170-180C and fry in small batches 3-4 minutes until golden and crisp; Drain on paper towels; serve hot with green chutney', 'spiced lentils, gram flour, rice flour, green chilli, ginger, turmeric, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Pyaaz Kachori', 'Mix the spiced onion with 1 finely chopped onion, 1 green chilli, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1/2 tsp chilli powder and salt; bind well; Shape into even portions, or dip in a thick gram-flour batter; Heat oil to 170-180C and fry in small batches 3-4 minutes until golden and crisp; Drain on paper towels; serve hot with green chutney', 'spiced onion, gram flour, rice flour, green chilli, ginger, turmeric, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Vada Pav', 'Mix the potato fritter and bun with 1 finely chopped onion, 1 green chilli, 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1/2 tsp chilli powder and salt; bind well; Shape into even portions, or dip in a thick gram-flour batter; Heat oil to 170-180C and fry in small batches 3-4 minutes until golden and crisp; Drain on paper towels; serve hot with green chutney', 'potato fritter and bun, gram flour, rice flour, green chilli, ginger, turmeric, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Pav Bhaji', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a heavy pan; add 1 large finely chopped onion and saute 5-6 minutes until golden brown; Add 1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste and cook 1 minute until the raw smell disappears; Add 2 pureed tomatoes (or 3 tbsp tomato paste) and cook 4-5 minutes until the oil separates at the edges; Stir in 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; cook 1 minute; Add the mashed mixed vegetables with about 3/4 cup water, cover and simmer 10-12 minutes until cooked through and the gravy thickens; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp garam masala, swirl in 2 tbsp cream or whisked yogurt, and finish with chopped coriander; serve hot', 'mashed mixed vegetables, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Misal Pav', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a heavy pan; add 1 large finely chopped onion and saute 5-6 minutes until golden brown; Add 1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste and cook 1 minute until the raw smell disappears; Add 2 pureed tomatoes (or 3 tbsp tomato paste) and cook 4-5 minutes until the oil separates at the edges; Stir in 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; cook 1 minute; Add the sprouts curry and bun with about 3/4 cup water, cover and simmer 10-12 minutes until cooked through and the gravy thickens; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp garam masala, swirl in 2 tbsp cream or whisked yogurt, and finish with chopped coriander; serve hot', 'sprouts curry and bun, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Dabeli', 'Add the potato and bun base to a serving bowl; Drizzle 2 tbsp whisked yogurt, 1 tbsp tamarind chutney and 1 tsp green chutney; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp chaat masala, 1/4 tsp roasted cumin, a handful of sev and 2 tbsp chopped onion; Finish with coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve immediately while crisp', 'potato and bun, chaat masala, tamarind chutney, mint chutney, yogurt, sev, onion, coriander leaves, roasted cumin'),
