    ('Veg Manchurian', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the mixed vegetables and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'mixed vegetables, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
