    ('Paneer Chilli', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the paneer and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'paneer, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Veg Hakka Noodles', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the noodles and vegetables and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'noodles and vegetables, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Veg Fried Rice', 'Soak 1.5 cups basmati rice for 20 minutes; boil in 4-5 cups salted water with whole spices until 70% cooked, then drain; In 2 tbsp ghee, cook a rice and vegetables masala with 1 sliced onion, 1 tbsp ginger-garlic, 2 chopped tomatoes, 1/2 cup yogurt and 1 tbsp biryani spices until thick; Layer the par-boiled rice over the masala; scatter fried onions, mint, and 2 tbsp warm milk steeped with saffron; Cover tightly (seal the lid with dough or foil) and cook on dum on the lowest heat 18-20 minutes; Rest 5 minutes, then fluff gently with a fork and serve with raita', 'rice and vegetables, basmati rice, whole spices, onion, yogurt, salt, ghee, mint, coriander leaves'),
    ('Schezwan Noodles', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the noodles and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'noodles, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Chilli Potato', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the potato and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'potato, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
