    ('Chicken Hakka Noodles', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the noodles and chicken and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'noodles and chicken, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Chicken Lollipop', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a kadai on medium heat and crackle 1 tsp cumin seeds; Add the chicken and saute on medium-high for 3-4 minutes; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp turmeric, 1 tsp red chilli powder, 1.5 tsp coriander powder and 3/4 tsp salt; toss to coat evenly; Cover and cook on low 8-10 minutes, stirring every couple of minutes, until tender and lightly caramelised; Uncover and raise the heat for 2 minutes to dry off moisture; Finish with 1/2 tsp garam masala and a handful of fresh coriander; serve hot', 'chicken, onion, tomato, ginger, garlic, cumin, turmeric, red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala, salt, oil, coriander leaves'),
    ('Egg Fried Rice', 'Soak 1.5 cups basmati rice for 20 minutes; boil in 4-5 cups salted water with whole spices until 70% cooked, then drain; In 2 tbsp ghee, cook a rice and egg masala with 1 sliced onion, 1 tbsp ginger-garlic, 2 chopped tomatoes, 1/2 cup yogurt and 1 tbsp biryani spices until thick; Layer the par-boiled rice over the masala; scatter fried onions, mint, and 2 tbsp warm milk steeped with saffron; Cover tightly (seal the lid with dough or foil) and cook on dum on the lowest heat 18-20 minutes; Rest 5 minutes, then fluff gently with a fork and serve with raita', 'rice and egg, basmati rice, whole spices, onion, yogurt, salt, ghee, mint, coriander leaves'),
    ('Gulab Jamun', 'Make a smooth batter or dough for the milk solids and rest 10 minutes; Boil 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water, 2 cardamoms and a few saffron strands to a 1-string syrup; keep warm; Fry on low-medium heat (about 160C) until evenly golden, turning often; Soak the hot fritters in the warm syrup 15-20 minutes until plump; Rest and serve', 'milk solids, sugar, ghee, cardamom, saffron, water'),
    ('Jalebi', 'Make a smooth batter or dough for the fermented batter and rest 10 minutes; Boil 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water, 2 cardamoms and a few saffron strands to a 1-string syrup; keep warm; Fry on low-medium heat (about 160C) until evenly golden, turning often; Soak the hot fritters in the warm syrup 15-20 minutes until plump; Rest and serve', 'fermented batter, sugar, ghee, cardamom, saffron, water'),
    ('Rasgulla', 'Make a smooth batter or dough for the chhena and rest 10 minutes; Boil 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water, 2 cardamoms and a few saffron strands to a 1-string syrup; keep warm; Fry on low-medium heat (about 160C) until evenly golden, turning often; Soak the hot fritters in the warm syrup 15-20 minutes until plump; Rest and serve', 'chhena, sugar, ghee, cardamom, saffron, water'),
