    ('Corn Bhel', 'Add the sweet corn base to a serving bowl; Drizzle 2 tbsp whisked yogurt, 1 tbsp tamarind chutney and 1 tsp green chutney; Sprinkle 1/2 tsp chaat masala, 1/4 tsp roasted cumin, a handful of sev and 2 tbsp chopped onion; Finish with coriander and a squeeze of lemon; serve immediately while crisp', 'sweet corn, chaat masala, tamarind chutney, mint chutney, yogurt, sev, onion, coriander leaves, roasted cumin'),
    ('Kalakand', 'Cook the milk and paneer with 2 cups full-fat milk and 1 tbsp ghee on low heat, stirring often so it doesn''t catch; When it thickens, add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 tsp cardamom powder; keep stirring 8-10 minutes; Cook until it leaves the sides of the pan and turns glossy; Garnish with 2 tbsp chopped nuts; serve warm or chilled', 'milk and paneer, sugar, milk, ghee, cardamom, chopped nuts'),
