    ('Rajbhog', 'Make a smooth batter or dough for the chhena and saffron and rest 10 minutes; Boil 1 cup sugar with 1/2 cup water, 2 cardamoms and a few saffron strands to a 1-string syrup; keep warm; Fry on low-medium heat (about 160C) until evenly golden, turning often; Soak the hot fritters in the warm syrup 15-20 minutes until plump; Rest and serve', 'chhena and saffron, sugar, ghee, cardamom, saffron, water'),
